commText: Welcome back for the chase. KKR persist with the same opening pair. Impact sub for RCB: IN - Vijaykumar Vyshak | OUT - Dinesh Karthik. Here's Siraj...

Cameron Green: Pretty happy with it (total), we saw how the pitch was playing, the off-cutters obviously working, hopefully it stays the same in the second innings. We have to wait and see. (Batting at three) I love playing there. You've got a bit more freedom in the last couple of overs in the powerplay. It's always nice to bat with Virat, he looked beautiful again today. There's certain bowlers in their team that I have never faced before. Obviously he has faced some 10 or 20 times, the experience is always amazing. They had a pretty good blueprint, cutters into the wicket - holding and not bouncing even, we have to wait and see if the dew comes in.
KKR bowling \nAndre Russell and Anukul Roy: 2/35 from 6 overs (ER: 5.83) \nOthers: 2/146 from 14 overs (ER: 10.43)
Dinesh Karthik vs LA Fast in the IPL since 2019 Runs: 316 Balls: 149 Dismissals: 6 Avg: 52.66 SR: 212.08 4s/6s: 31/20
Double of 1000 runs and 100 wickets in the IPL (2724, 152) - Ravindra Jadeja (2326, 100) - Andre Russell (1560, 183) - Dwayne Bravo (1454, 113) - Axar Patel (1048, 165) - Sunil Narine

21:05 Local Time, 15:35 GMT, 21:05 IST: RCB will be happy with this score. As the innings progressed, the pitch became slower and it was tough to hit on the rise. And KKR took pace off nicely and when they gave the batters pace, it was put away. Once again Kohli led the way, with his innings of 83. He started off aggressively in the powerplay, then settled down to nudge it around in the middle overs and again opened out at the death. Faf went early but Green, Maxwell and DK at the end contributed well to help Kohli who was the main man during that innings. KKR's fielding was a let-down as they dropped Maxwell twice and Starc once again proved to be expensive which should be a worry. The powerplay is when the ball comes on nicely and that's where the chase will be key. Back for KKR's reply in 5 minutes...

Starc to Kohli, out Karthik Run Out!! Last ball and there's a run-out. A wide slower ball outside off, Kohli shuffles across but can't lay bat on ball, they try to sneak a bye, but Philip Salt hits direct with an under-arm throw. DK did not dive and is caught short. Karthik run out (Philip Salt) 20(8) [6s-3]
Starc to Kohli, THATS OUT!! Run Out!!
A direct-hit and Karthik looks to be gone. Yes he is.
Starc to Karthik, 1 run, slower ball off-cutter on a back of a length outside off, slapped to deep extra-cover for one
Starc to Karthik, SIX, poor bowling and six more. Full and down leg, Karthik gets inside the line and flicks it away over fine-leg
Starc to Kohli, 1 run, slower short ball outside off, Kohli pulls to deep square leg and he is happy with just one
Starc to Kohli, SIX, into the crowd at deep mid-wicket. A slower ball off-cutter full on the stumps, whipped with such strong wrists over deep mid-wicket
Starc to Kohli, 2 runs, Kohli comes down the track and whips it to Ramandeep at deep mid-wicket, takes him on and gets in despite the direct-hit
Mitchell Starc [3.0-0-31-0] is back into the attack
A direct-hit and Kohli is confident. He is in.

Russell to Karthik, SIX, pace-on and again six. A short of length delivery outside off, Karthik did not get all on the pull, but manages to clear long-on and these are not the biggest boundaries in the world anyway
Russell to Karthik, no run, dug in slower and Karthik was rising on his tiptoes to upper-cut, misses, reviews for a wide, but the third ump feels that it is just about fine
DK reviews for a non-wide. Fair delivery and a dot.
Russell to Karthik, SIX, pace on and Karthik takes full toll, seam-up, full outside off, slammed flat over long-off
Russell to Karthik, no run, slower ball off-cutter on off, defended back, really strange batting this is
Russell to Karthik, no run, tight good length delivery on off, defended back, a precious dot
Russell to Kohli, 1 run, short of length outside off, Kohli pulls to deep mid-wicket
Harshit Rana to Kohli, 1 run, just fast slower ball off-cutters from Harshit Rana, Kohli comes down the track and swipes to deep mid-wicket but just one
Harshit Rana to Kohli, no run, slower ball off-cutter outside off, Kohli tries to cut too hard and inside-edges it backon to the feet
Harshit Rana to Karthik, 1 run, slower ball off-cutter on middle, nudged to deep backward square leg
Dinesh Karthik, right handed bat, comes to the crease

Harshit Rana to Anuj Rawat, out Caught by Philip Salt!! Edged and gone. A slower ball off-cutter full outside off, Anuj Rawat throws the bat at it, edges it behind, Philip Salt takes it low on the dive. Anuj Rawat c Philip Salt b Harshit Rana 3(3)
Harshit Rana to Anuj Rawat, THATS OUT!! Caught!!
Harshit Rana to Kohli, 1 run, slower ball off-cutter on off, wristed to deep square leg
Harshit Rana to Kohli, 2 runs, slower ball off-cutter full outside off, heaved to deep mid-wicket, just one but a direct-hit at the bowler's end, the ricochet allows the 2nd, Russell is not happy
Harshit Rana [3.0-0-34-1] is back into the attack
KRR have made their impact sub - Chakaravarthy out, Raghuvanshi in.
Russell to Kohli, 1 run, slower ball full on the pads, Kohli flicks and it's a top-edge on to helmet, rolls to point
Russell to Anuj Rawat, 1 run, dropped by Chakaravarthy at short third man. A slower short of length delivery outside off, guided low and on the dive forward, the spinner can't hang on
Russell to Anuj Rawat, 2 runs, short of length on off, pulled wide of deep mid-wicket for a quick two
Anuj Rawat, left handed bat, comes to the crease

Russell to Rajat Patidar, out Caught by Rinku Singh!! Straight to deep mid-wicket. A slower ball off-cutter on off, pulled to perfection to find Rinku at deep mid-wicket. Rajat Patidar fails again. Rajat Patidar c Rinku Singh b Russell 3(4)
Russell to Rajat Patidar, THATS OUT!! Caught!!
Russell to Rajat Patidar, wide, dug in short outside off, pacy stuff, Rajat Patidar can't reach it and wide called
Russell to Kohli, 1 run, fullish outside off, Kohli drives on the rise, but straight to the fielder at long-off
Russell to Rajat Patidar, 1 run, slower ball off-cutter on off, Rajat Patidar pulls to long-on
Andre Russell [2.0-0-9-1] is back into the attack
"Gambhir and Kohli hug at the strategic timeout," informs Kaushik from the stadium. "A small convo there - quick meet and (pleasantly) greet."
Timeout! The pitch has shown signs of slowing down and the cutters are working nicely. 180 should be a very good score.
Starc to Kohli, FOUR, tremendous blow to finish off. A slower ball off-cutter full outside off, Kohli lofts wide of long-off, one bounce over the ropes, held his shape and did not try to overhit
Starc to Kohli, wide, dug in short on the stumps, too short, Kohli pulls and misses, Philip Salt fumbles and wide called
Starc to Kohli, no run, great over so far this, slower ball off-cutter wide outside off, Kohli cuts and misses
Starc to Rajat Patidar, 1 run, short of length down leg, Rajat Patidar mistimes the pull but gets a single to deep backward square leg
Starc to Kohli, 1 run, slower ball off-cutter dug in, Kohli comes down the track to bunt it to long-on
Starc to Kohli, no run, again the change of pace, slower ball full outside off, Kohli gets forward to drive, thick inside-edge rolls to Philip Salt, Kohli has a wry smile on his face
Starc to Kohli, no run, slower ball off-cutter on middle, Kohli swipes and misses, bounces over middle-stump, so lucky
Mitchell Starc [2.0-0-24-0] is back into the attack
Narine to Kohli, 1 run, slower offbreak on off, Kohli tries to pull too hard, thick inside-edge rolls to short fine-leg for one

Narine to Kohli, 2 runs, only Kohli could have made that 2nd. Shows his fitness even though he is breathing heavily now. Slashes the flat delivery wide of Rinku at sweeper cover, takes him on and it's a good throw back to Philip Salt who whips the bails off, Kohli is in with a full-length dive, straining every sinew in his body to get in
Narine to Kohli, FOUR, tossed up offbreak outside the leg-stump, Kohli makes room and slogsweeps, there is deep mid-wicket but this is placed wide of the fielder
Narine to Kohli, 2 runs, fullish on the stumps, flicked in front of deep mid-wicket and they race through for the 2nd, great running that
Narine to Rajat Patidar, 1 run, fullish outside off, goes away, Rajat Patidar gets forward to push it wide of cover, is off the mark
Rajat Patidar, right handed bat, comes to the crease
Maxwell vs Narine in the IPL Runs: 62 Balls: 64 Dismissals: 4 Avg: 15.5 SR: 96.87 4s/6s: 5/1 Dots: 28

Narine to Maxwell, out Caught by Rinku Singh!! Finally they catch Maxwell. Maxwell though is not happy, curses himself off. He makes room to slash and it's a thick top-edge, flies to sweeper cover and Rinku comes around to grab it. Narine puts his head down and does not even offer any emotion. Maxwell c Rinku Singh b Narine 28(19) [4s-3 6s-1]
Narine to Maxwell, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Highlights (Overs 7-14) -- 63/1 -- Scoring rate slows down after powerplay -- Ball starts gripping more as it gets older -- Russell knocks over Green for 33 (8.6) -- Varun goes for 17 in his 2nd over; RCB break shackles -- Maxwell dropped on 11 and 21
Harshit Rana to Maxwell, 1 run, slower ball off-cutter on a length on the stumps, swung to deep square leg
Harshit Rana to Maxwell, FOUR, very full outside off, Maxwell opens the face of the bat and glides it between backward point and short third man, right into the gap

Harshit Rana to Maxwell, 2 runs, dropped by Narine at short third man. A slower ball off-cutter outside off, Maxwell slogs widly, thick outside-edge loops to Narine who shells it going back, never a great fielder Narine but that should have been taken. Harshit Rana can't believe his luck
Harshit Rana to Maxwell, SIX, looked a miscue but it goes over Starc's head at long-on. A short of length delivery outside off, Maxwell pulls and gets enough on it
Harshit Rana to Kohli, 1 run, fullish on off, driven with no timing to long-on
Harshit Rana to Maxwell, 1 run, slower ball off-cutter full outside off, Maxwell drives to sweeper cover
Harshit Rana [2.0-0-19-1] is back into the attack
Narine to Maxwell, 1 run, full and at the toes of Maxwell who gets forward to drive to long-on
Narine to Kohli, 1 run, fullish on leg-stump, flicked to deep mid-wicket
Narine to Maxwell, 1 run, fullish outside off, knocked down to long-on
Narine to Kohli, 1 run, tossed up full outside off, driven to long-off
Narine to Maxwell, 1 run, dropped by Ramandeep! Such a simple catch too, Maxwell makes room and skies the loft, more height than distance and Ramandeep at deep mid-wicket puts it down
Narine to Maxwell, no run, the offbreak turns back into middle and leg, Maxwell goes on the back foot to flick it away, misses
Sunil Narine [2.0-0-25-0] is back into the attack
Chakaravarthy to Maxwell, 1 run, length on the stumps, nudged to mid-wicket and Chakaravarthy gives chase to keep it to one
Most sixes for RCB in the IPL 240 - Virat Kohli 239 - Chris Gayle 238 - AB de Villiers 67 - Glenn Maxwell 50 - Faf du Plessis
Chakaravarthy to Maxwell, FOUR, Maxwell hits it straight down the ground as long-off was moved after the last ball. Again he makes room and there's no spin, flat-batted
Chakaravarthy to Maxwell, FOUR, Maxwell now takes Chakaravarthy on, makes room and blasts the drive wide of extra-cover, taken from a length and put away
Chakaravarthy to Kohli, 1 run, back of a length around off, Kohli pulls to deep mid-wicket and that's 50 for Kohli, gives the thumbs up to someone
Chakaravarthy round the wicket.
Chakaravarthy to Kohli, SIX, it was tight for the last few overs and Kohli breaks the shackles, on a length on the stumps, Kohli gets forward and swings it over deep mid-wicket, sails away
Chakaravarthy to Maxwell, 1 run, very full, drifting into leg-stump, driven to long-on

Russell to Maxwell, byes, 1 run, lovely delivery, slower ball off-cutter on a length just outside off, Maxwell is beaten on the push, the ball bounces in front of Philip Salt and they sneak a bye, the throw hits Maxwell on the back, but he should be fine
Russell to Maxwell, no run, Maxwell is very lucky, slower ball down leg, he is into the swipe too early, leading-edge on to arm and it doesn't carry to Russell or Philip Salt
Russell to Maxwell, no run, good length just outside off, Maxwell tries to run it down and misses
Russell to Kohli, 1 run, seam-up back of a length delivery on off, defended past Russell
Russell to Kohli, no run, another off-pace delivery dug in, just rises above stump-height, Kohli pulls and misses, just wide of off-stump
Kohli's six off Narine was the 1500th maximum for RCB in the IPL, only MI have hit more (1575).
Russell to Kohli, no run, slower ball dug in as Kohli gives the charge to pull, misses
Chakaravarthy to Maxwell, no run, fired down leg, Maxwell flicks and misses, off the pad and no chance of a legbye as the ball is near Philip Salt
Chakaravarthy to Kohli, 1 run, flat good length on off, Kohli punches wide of cover
Chakaravarthy to Kohli, no run, fired into the pads, going down, Kohli flicks and misses
Chakaravarthy to Kohli, no run, flat good length outside off, dabbed straight to the fielder at short third man
Chakaravarthy to Maxwell, 1 run, tossed up legbreak full outside off, Maxwell opens the face of the bat to drive wide of point, is off the mark
Chakaravarthy to Kohli, 1 run, flat good length on middle-stump, turned to deep mid-wicket for one
Varun Chakaravarthy, right-arm leg break, comes into the attack
Glenn Maxwell, right handed bat, comes to the crease

Russell to Green, out Bowled!! Knocked him over. Off the pads and on to middle-stump. Full and angling into the pads, down the leg-side, Green flicks and misses, off the pad and that's an unlcuky way to go. But Green has played a nice innings. Green b Russell 33(21) [4s-4 6s-2]
Russell to Green, THATS OUT!! Bowled!!
Russell to Green, SIX, friendly low full-toss on the pads, flicked away over deep backward square leg, easy for Green
Russell to Green, no run, so close! A slower ball off-cutter on the stumps, Green turns the bat-face, gets a thin inside-edge that bounces over the stumps, Philip Salt dives to his left to stop
Russell to Kohli, 1 run, a low full-toss on the stumps, flicked to deep mid-wicket
Russell to Kohli, no run, slower ball off-cutter outside off, Kohli gets forward to swipe, gets a thin inside-edge on the bounce to Philip Salt
Russell to Green, 1 run, good length on off, run-down to third man
Andre Russell, right-arm fast, comes into the attack
Narine to Kohli, no run, pushed through on off, slides straight on, Kohli gets a soft outer half on the push back to Narine
Narine to Kohli, SIX, slightly overcooks the length and pays the price, tossed up offbreak on off, the slogsweep and Kohli nails it, over deep mid-wicket
Narine to Kohli, no run, flat offbreak that turns back in to off, bunted back
Narine to Kohli, 2 runs, extra bounce outside off, Kohli gets on top of it and punches over extra-cover for two, long chase for long-off who gets across and cuts it off
Narine to Green, 1 run, flat back of a length on the stumps, Green makes room and cuts to sweeper cover
Narine to Kohli, 1 run, tossed up full on the stumps, swatted hard to long-on
Anukul Roy to Kohli, 1 run, flat good length on the stumps, nudged through the vacant mid-wicket area
Anukul Roy to Green, 1 run, fullish outside off, Green mistimes the drive to cover and they rush through for a quick single
Anukul Roy to Green, no run, yorker length on the stumps, Green squuezes it out to short third man
Anukul Roy to Green, no run, quicker good length on the stumps, dabbed to backward point and again Kohli is sent back
Anukul Roy to Green, no run, short and wide outside off, Green misses out, cuts to cover
Kohli in powerplay in the IPL since 2023 Runs: 367 Balls: 264 Dismissals: 4 Avg: 91.75 SR: 139.01 4s/6s: 51/5 Dots: 95
Anukul Roy to Kohli, 1 run, good length and sliding on, Kohli goes on the back foot to pull to deep mid-wicket

Powerplay summary -- Kohli, Green get RCB off to another quick start -- No swing early on for pacers -- Pitch is on the drier side -- Harshit removes Faf for 8 -- Starc slightly unlucky with edges going for four -- Green takes the attack to Narine in his 1st over
Timeout! RCB have had a great powerplay. They need at least 200 to test this KKR lineup.
Narine to Green, SIX, Green uses the long handle well there, makes room and takes the tossed up offbreak on the stumps, lofts and it flies away over long-on, clean strike
Narine to Green, FOUR, short and wide outside off, Green smashes the cut wide of cover, too much width and put away
Narine to Green, FOUR, tossed up offbreak on the stumps, Green swings it with the spin, wide of backward square leg and it runs away
Narine to Green, no run, cramps Green up with that middle and leg line, Green makes room to cut to cover-point
Narine to Green, no run, good length offbreak turns into off and middle, Green makes room and cuts to cover-point
Narine to Kohli, 1 run, tossed up offbreak full outside off, Kohli wrists it to square leg and Starc is slow, Green gets in
Sunil Narine, right-arm off break, comes into the attack
Anukul Roy to Green, no run, quick and beats Green on the inside-edge outside the leg-stump, Philip Salt can't gather, Kohli wants a bye to short third man but Green sends him back
Anukul Roy to Green, no run, short and wide outside off, cut to extra-cover who dives to his left and stops, Green hurries back
Anukul Roy to Green, no run, flat and attacking leg-stump, punched to mid-on
Anukul Roy to Green, 2 runs, drifting into leg-stump, flicked wide of deep mid-wicket and an easy two
Anukul Roy to Kohli, 1 run, tossed up outside the leg-stump, Kohli now makes room and drives to long-off
Anukul Roy to Kohli, no run, tossed up full outside the leg-stump, Kohli gets forward to drive hard and straight to mid-on
Anukul Roy, Left arm orthodox, comes into the attack
Harshit Rana to Green, FOUR, dug in short outside off, to the tall Green who upper-cuts over short third man, poor ball with the fielder inside the ring

Harshit Rana to Green, no run, clear run-out chance goes. A short of length delivery outside off, punched to cover-point and Ramandeep can't grab hold of the ball, both batters were halfway down the track and meeting each other, the chance goes
Harshit Rana to Kohli, 1 run, short of length and seam-up outside off, pulled hard and straight to deep square leg
"Between balls Kohli seems to be passing a message to the dug out about tennis-ball type bounce from back of the length," spots Kaushik
Harshit Rana to Kohli, no run, short of length outside off, slower and Kohli pulls and misses
Harshit Rana to Kohli, 2 runs, short of length outside off, slashed over cover-point and again Ramandeep it is, chases and pulls it back
Harshit Rana to Kohli, 2 runs, slower ball off-cutter outside off, Kohli cuts wide of point and Ramandeep dives to his left and takes the pace off the shot, still two

Starc to Green, FOUR, no luck so far for Starc. Full on off, shaping away, Green gets forward to drive, thick outside-edge flies wide of the dive of Harshit Rana at short third man, was in the air but just wide
Starc to Kohli, 1 run, short of length on the body, nudged to square leg for one
Starc to Kohli, 2 runs, Rinku again so rapid, short of length on off, defended wide of short third man and it is purring across, Rinku from deep backward point gets across and cuts it off to save two

Starc to Kohli, FOUR, now he gets lucky. Is late on this back of a length delivery on the stumps, has the bat angled and the thick inside-edge flies over the stumps and wide of Philip Salt, Kohli and Starc exchange wry smiles

Starc to Kohli, SIX, that's Kohli at his very best. A slower ball off-cutter on leg-stump, full and dismissed over deep square leg with a whip of the wrists, that snap when Kohli flicks, wow, flies away, minimal followthrough as well and Kohli loved that
Starc to Kohli, no run, tight and fullish on the stumps, Kohli is neatly behind that as he gets forward to defend
Cameron Green, right handed bat, comes to the crease

Harshit Rana to du Plessis, out Caught by Starc!! First dagger into RCB fans' hearts. They are stunned. du Plessis falls to the scoop, was the slower ball off-cutter outside off, du Plessis shuffles across to scoop, plinks a tame catch to short fine-leg. Harshit Rana is away on his celebration, no flying kiss this time - maybe that's reserved for someone special tonight. du Plessis c Starc b Harshit Rana 8(6) [6s-1]
Harshit Rana to du Plessis, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Harshit Rana to du Plessis, SIX, du Plessis got lucky there, he premeditated the scoop, but then saw the line outside off and just held the bat open, it flies away from there and all the way over third man, certainly did not meant it to go there but he will take it
Harshit Rana to Kohli, 1 run, back of a length and angling into middle, swung away to deep backward square leg and Rinku is so quick, gets across and cuts it off, Harshit Rana applauds that effort
Harshit Rana to du Plessis, 1 run, short of length and at the body of du Plessis who nudges it to backward square leg for one
Harshit Rana to du Plessis, wide, dug in short and way too short at du Plessis, left alone, wide called
Harshit Rana to Kohli, 1 run, fullish around off, Kohli opens the face of the bat and pushes it firmly to deep backward point
A wide slip now goes out.
Harshit Rana to Kohli, no run, short of length outside off, Kohli guides with an open face to short third man, slightly outside-edgy this as well
Harshit Rana, right-arm fast medium, comes into the attack
Starc to du Plessis, no run, full on the stumps, driven to mid-off and crisply, straight to the fielder and du Plessis puts his head back in disappointment
Starc to du Plessis, no run, short of length and tucks up du Plessis on middle, defended back
Starc to Kohli, 1 run, short of length and rising at Kohli, threatening the splice, Kohli adjusts and gets it down, through backward point for one
Shouts of "Kohli" do the rounds.
Starc to du Plessis, 1 run, full outside off, du Plessis bottom-hands the drive wide of mid-off and sets off, takes on Shreyas Iyer's forward flick and makes it, no direct-hit
Starc to Kohli, 1 run, pitched up outside off, Kohli slices the square drive, in the air but in the gap, flies to deep backward point

Starc to Kohli, FOUR, thick outside-edge and it runs away, wide of the diving short third man to his right, length and angling away from Kohli who pushes and gets lucky, went to ground quickly, Starc has a wry smile on his face
Kohli and du Plessis are at the crease. Kohli is on strike. Starc will open the attack
